# 8. 次はどんな出会いが

Tsukasa: I hope you're ready, Rui!
Rui: Hehehe. I could say the same for you, Tsukasa.
Miyake: Alright, take your positions!
Miyake: For tonight's final pillow fight, we have Tenma versus Kamishiro! Gentlemen, let's rumble!
Tsukasa: *Roar*
Rui: Ah, a triple throw right out of the gates! Unfortunately for you...
Rui: I watched what you did against Miyake, so that's not going to work on me!
Hayashi: What?! He dodged them?! By spinning?!
Taniyama: Cool! Go Kamishiro!
Miyake: H-Hey, you guys... If you break any of the inn's stuff, you're automatically disqualified!
Miyake: The first to get hit five times loses, but this is probably gonna take a while...
Rui: Now it's my turn! Let's see how you deal with a pillow bombing!
Miyake: Huh...?! He just threw all the pillows into the air...!
Hayashi: Wait, that means...
Taniyama: They're gonna hit us! Wah!
Tsukasa: Hmph... That was clever, but I narrowly avoided all of them!
Rui: Ah, impressive... Hm...?
Hayashi: What's the big idea, Kamishiro...? Those landed right on top of us...
Taniyama: Yeah, what he said! We're fighting for Tenma now!
Rui: Oh? I thought we were supposed to fight as individuals. Three versus one seems a bit unfair, no?
Miyake: Y-Yeah! We decided from the start that it should be one-on-one...
Rui: No matter...
Rui: Miyake, you're my last hope.
Miyake: Huh?! What do you mean?!
Tsukasa: Ah, you fight even though you're outnumbered! That is commendable! Comrades, prepare for battle!!
Hayashi & Taniyama: Roger!
Rui: Hehe... We may be fewer in number, but we still plan on winning. I hope you're prepared to have your confidence shattered.
Tsukasa: No, victory shall be ours! Attaaack...!!!
Miyake: W-Wait, stop! If we fight all at once—
Teacher: Boys, it's past curfew! What's going on here?!
Tsukasa & Rui: Huh?! Oh...
Miyake: I knew this would happen...
Teacher: That's two nights in a row. I'll be asking for letters of apology from each of you.
Teacher: Come get me once you've finished writing them. I'll escort you back to your rooms after that.
Teacher: *Sigh* Honestly, does the Weirdo Wombo Combo ever learn...?
Tsukasa: Grr...! How could I have made such a foolish mistake...?!
Tsukasa: Not only am I a class representative, I am a future star! I'm supposed to lead by example, but I've been scolded two days in a row by the teachers!
Rui: Yes, we did go a little too far back there...
Rui: Still, this has all been so new for me.
Tsukasa: New?
Rui: Yes, between our pillow fight...
Rui: ...sightseeing with everyone...
Rui: ...getting separated, reuniting with everyone and seeing the parade together...
Rui: They all felt like new experiences. It felt like I was working on a show. That sort of wonderment...
Rui: I'm so glad that I got to spend this time with you and the others today.
Tsukasa: Rui...
Rui: And I have you to thank, Tsukasa.
Tsukasa: Me?
Rui: Yes. Miyake actually mentioned something earlier...
Miyake: *Sigh* Today was so much fun. I'm glad you decided to join our group, Kamishiro!
Rui: You are? Hehe. I really appreciate it.
Miyake: Of course. I got to know you a little better, and...
Miyake: To tell you the truth...
Miyake: When you first transferred to our school, Rui, you always seemed to have fun tinkering with your drones and stuff at your desk...
Miyake: But there were also times when you looked really bored.
Rui: That apparently made him think that he had better not disturb me...
Rui: But then, he said that I began smiling more after I began spending more time with you, Tsukasa.
Rui: As a result, he decided that he wanted to get to know me better.
Tsukasa: Oh, I had no idea...
Rui: Yes, well...
Rui: I believe it's evidence of just how much I've changed.
Rui: How about we take a group photo together?
Tsukasa: A group photo?
Rui: Yes. I'd like to have something to commemorate this day with.
Rui: (Tsukasa was right in saying that I never usually make such suggestions.)
Rui: (But I probably said that because the time we spent together is so precious to me.)
Rui: The old me was convinced that I'd never be able to actually get along with anyone.
Rui: But that began to change after we started doing shows together at the Wonder Stage.
Rui: Now, I don't need shows or anything to get to know someone. On top of that, I want to share smiles and laughter with them.
Rui: So, Tsukasa... Thank you for giving me the opportunity to change the way I have.
Tsukasa: I see...
Tsukasa: The only response I can give right now is, “You're welcome!”
Tsukasa: Still... I don't think I deserve all the credit.
Rui: What?
Tsukasa: Think about it, Rui. If you were firmly against changing, then it wouldn't have mattered what I did. Things would've remained the way they were.
Tsukasa: However, you wanted to be a part of a group, and you've been having fun as a result.
Tsukasa: And that has nothing to do with me... You're here today because that's what you chose.
Rui: Yes, you may be right...
Tsukasa: Also, there's something else that I need to ask you!
Rui: Yes?
Tsukasa: Why are you talking like everything's in the past already?! Our trip is not yet over!
Tsukasa: We should keep having fun until we all have to go home!
Rui: Yes, I agree!
Rui: Which means we should go over once more what we'll be doing tomorrow. How does an early-morning walk along the Kamo River sound? Don't worry, I'll ask the teachers for permission.
Tsukasa: Ah, that sounds splendid! We can watch the sunrise while we're there! What a way to spend our youth! Saki will surely enjoy hearing about it!
Tsukasa: Also! We should try skipping stones!
Rui: Skipping stones...? Oh, when you try to get flat rocks to bounce across water?
Tsukasa: Wait, have you never tried? Okay, watch! You hold it like this and flick your wrist!
Rui: Hehehe... Your form seems a bit odd.
Tsukasa: What do you mean?! You can get stones to skip endlessly by doing this! Skip! Skip! Skip! Oh...
Teacher: Tenma! What's all this about?! “Skip! Skip! Skip!”?!
Tsukasa: Argh! What are you doing here?!
Teacher: You didn't think anyone would hear you shouting?! Also, where's that letter of apology I asked for?!
Tsukasa: Nooo, I'm sorry! It slipped my mind while talking with Rui here...
Teacher: But it looks like he already wrote his.
Tsukasa: What?! R-Rui, how?! When...?!
Rui: I finished writing it before you came to talk to me.
Tsukasa: T-Traitor...!
Teacher: Finish writing it already, Tenma! There's a teachers-only party that I'm not about to miss!
Tsukasa: O-Okay, I will!
Rui: (Hehe. Sorry, Tsukasa...)
Rui: (But this is also going in my album of precious memories.)
Rui: (Tsukasa's given me so many reasons to smile.)
Rui: (Which has in turn allowed me to make new friends and establish new connections.)
Rui: I wonder what the future has in store for me next...
